#Train and test split

  #2. Logistic Regression

# train test split
set.seed(123)
split <- sample.split(df$class,
                      SplitRatio = 0.80)
df.train <- subset(df,
                   split == TRUE)
df.test <- subset(subset(df,
                         split == FALSE))

# Fitting K-NN to the Training set and Predicting the Test set results
y_pred = knn(train = df.train1,
             test = df.test1,
             df.train1$class,
             k = 9)

head(y_pred)
## [1] 0 0 0 0 1 0
## Levels: 0 1
misclass.error = mean(df.test1$class != y_pred)
misclass.error
## [1] 0.02189781
#Misclass error with optimal K value of 9 = 0.02189781
#Choosing a K-value
y_pred <- NULL
error.rate <- NULL

for (i in 1:20){
  set.seed(123)
  y_pred <- knn(train = df.train1,
                test = df.test1,
                df.train1$class,
                k = i)
  error.rate[i] <- mean(df.test1$class != y_pred)
}

error.rate

## [19] 0.03649635 0.02919708
#Visualize K - Elbow Method

k.values <- 1:20
error.df <- data.frame(error.rate,
                       k.values)

       aes(k.values,
           error.rate)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(lty = "dotted",
            color = "red")

##SVM Models

# Fitting SVM to the Training set
classifier = svm(formula = class ~ .,
                 data = df.train,
                 kernel = 'radial')

# Predicting the Test set results
y_pred = predict(classifier,
                 newdata = df.test[-10])

# Making the Confusion Matrix
cm = table(df.test$class, y_pred)
summary(classifier)

#Tune hyper parameters
tune.results <- tune(svm, 
                     train.x = df.train[, -10],
                     train.y = df.train[, 10], 
                     kernel = 'radial',
                     ranges = list(cost = 10^(-1:2),
                                 gamma = c(0.25,.5,1,2)))

# list(cost=10^(-1:2),
#      gamma=c(0.25,.5,1,2))
